<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
    <title>Devlog</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/style.css" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/coldark.css" />
    <link rel="shortcut icon" type="image/x-icon" href="/assets/favicon.ico" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <nav class="p-5 bg-gray-800">
      <a class="text-teal-400 font-semibold" href="/">Devlog</a>
    </nav>
    <main class="my-8 md:px-8 grid grid-template-main">
      <div class="text-sm col-start-3 col-end-4">
        <section class="mb-12 space-y-2">
          <p>
            <strong class="text-rose-400">You've found my devlog!</strong>
            Here I'm trying to collect ideas and thoughts, new findings, and
            reminders regarding software development. I see it as a
            <a
              class="text-indigo-400"
              href="https://www.buildingasecondbrain.com/"
              >second brain</a
            >
            for all things related to development. It's also also a way for me
            to practice
            <a class="text-teal-400 group" href="/pages/learning-in-public">
              <span class="text-gray-500 group-hover:text-yellow-500">[[</span>
              Learning in public
              <span class="text-gray-500 group-hover:text-yellow-500"
                >]]</span
              > </a
            >.
          </p>
          <p>
            The content is created in
            <a class="text-indigo-400" href="https://logseq.com/">Logseq</a>,
            exported to JSON and then generated as static HTML.
          </p>
        </section>
        {% block content %}
        {{ content | safe }}
        {% endblock %}
      </div>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
